result.execSummary:
The defendant Tommy R Hines was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Cocaine/Coca, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(c).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by: 

The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 10 MONTHS at the House of Corrections with 47 days credit CONSECUTIVE to the sentences in case #15CF553 and 14CF4899. Court will allow for goodtime credit. Court will allow for release to the Day Reporting Center for treatment and education. No electronic monitoring.

Court ordered the defendant's driving privileges be suspended for 18 months.

Court will allow for expungement if the defendant is in complete compliance with the sentence.

Defendant Tommy R Hines in court with attorney David P. Kaiser.  Defendant Tommy R Hines in custody.  Tyrone Martin St. Junior appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Tommy R Hines in court with attorney David M. Kaiser.  Defendant Tommy R Hines in custody.  Tyrone Martin St. Junior appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered Counts 2 and 3 dismissed and read-in to case for the purpose of sentencing.
As to Count 1:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Attorney David P. Kaiser in court, defendant Tommy R Hines not in court, in custody.  Jeremy R. Arn appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense motion for modification heard.  Court modifies bail to $1,500.00 cash with same previous terms and conditions of release.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for June 22, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
Notice of Motion and Motion to Modify Bail, received and filed.
Bail motion by defense argued and denied by the Court.

Defendant Tommy R Hines in court with attorney David P. Kaiser.  Defendant Tommy R Hines in custody.  Tyrone Martin St. Junior appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Court took judicial notice of certified documents regarding case #14CF4899 that are attached to the complaint.  Sworn for the state:Michael Driscoll-MPD Officer.    State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Case is reassigned to Branch 21, Judge Brash due to a lower pending case.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and pleads not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 21.  Scheduling conference scheduled for June 4, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Court orders defendant TURNED OVER to JUSTICE Point for Supervision.  ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY/DEFENDANT to be monitored by drug testing.
   Court ordered no possession or use of controlled substances without a valid prescription AND no drug paraphernalia.
  No driving without a valid license.
  Defendant advised if released from custody it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.
Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping, a warrant issued or high cash bail.
